rComments: She is an amazing teacher. Her lectures are well organized and easy to follow. She is always kind and willing to answer any questions that you may have. She explains the historical context and its present impact on Latin America. She is a fair grader and always has office hours.
Very clear. She writes on board so you have time to actually copy the notes if you forget unlike some profs who just talks and talks and won't stop till your hands get all sore.

She is the type of professor who is passionate about her field of subject, and you'll see that and want to pay attention. But most importantly she wants you to do well. Not only do well, but wants you to engage your mind and understand what the whole big picture. Simply put, she is awesome and her teaching methods are great. awesome and genuine

She is a great prof, very nice and helpful. Structures lectures well and provides the opportunities for good note taking. No surprises on tests or exams and she gives you possible questions that could be on the exam.

Absolutely love Professor Rice! All her lectures are straightforward and easy to understand. Her readings are really interesting and I actually enjoyed reading them. Definitely recommend taking all courses with her (if she is coming back this year).

Best prof. ever. I am currently a graduate student, thanks to her. She is willing to help you with any problems, say class materials, essay, how to write an essay etc. She will not give you arbitrary answers. If you feel unjust about your grade, she will attend your concerns openly. I just need to say this again. Best. Prof. Ever.

Excellent professor. It's a breath of fresh air to see professors that actually care about their students, and their subject. Roberta Rice is one of those people. She's a good lecturer, so just pay attention and you'll be fine.

Thumbs up to the person who posted a rating message about Professor Rice on 5/2/10- I agree 100%! Take all classes you can take with Dr Rice because she knows how to teach and cares about her students. To all female students: stay away from Professor Paul Kingston.
I've taken 4 courses( POLB90+91, POLC90+99) with her since 2008.  Like another user said, she's one of those professors you'll remember for life.
